National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice released a statement expressing condolences on the death of Nelson Mandela, describing him as one of history's great leaders. She praised Mandela for his role in ending apartheid in South Africa and creating a nation of hope and healing. Rice emphasized Mandela's commitment to universal principles and his ability to transform minds and hearts. She called on others to celebrate Mandela's life by embracing values such as reconciliation, justice, freedom, and equality. Rice urged people to follow Mandela's example and strive for peaceful resolutions to conflicts and the power of empathy and human dignity. She concluded by stating that Mandela's legacy and example will continue to inspire South Africa and all of humanity.